Super Eagles left-back Jamilu Collins was in action for the entirety of the game while Ademola Lookman watched proceedings for the bench for the home team. Bayern Munich are closing in on the title after thrashing Bayer Leverkusen 4-2 at the BayArena (Leverkusen). Goals from Kingsley Coman, Leon Goretzka, Serge Gnabry and Robert Lewandowski gave the Bavarians victory; Lucas Alario on 10 minutes and Florian Wirtz in the 89th minute opened and closed the scoring during the encounter. Netherlands U19 star Joshua Zirkzee was a non-playing substitute for the tenth time in the Bundesliga this season. Let’s go to the Commerzbank-Arena where Eintracht Frankfurt entertained Taiwo Awoniyi’s Mainz 05. It ended 2-0 in favour of the visitors.  Manager Beierlorzer still kept faith with Awoniyi despite the striker firing blanks in three consecutive games and his barren spell continued today despite spending 90 minutes on the pitch. The Liverpool loanee received his first ever caution in the German top-flight two minutes after the restart. MoussaNiakhate and Pierre Kunde with the goals for Mainz. At the Merkur Spiel-Arena, Fortuna Dusseldorf and TSG Hoffenheim shared the spoils in a four-goal thriller. Hoffenheim’s former Germany U20 skipper Kevin Akpoguma watched proceedings from the bench. Rouwen Hennings bagged a brace for the Dusseldorf team while Munas Dabbur and Steven Zuber replied for Hoffenheim. In the evening kickoff, Jordan Torunarigha starts for Hertha BSC against Borussia Dortmund at Signal Iduna Park.